<p><b>Internal communications</b> includes all communication within an organization. Communication may be oral or written, face to face or virtual, one-on-one or in groups. Effective internal communication is a vital means of addressing organizational concerns. Clear and concise internal communication helps to establish formal roles and responsibilities for employees and maintain organization and clarity within an establishment.</p>
